cynthia liu is the stanford dining administrative program manager prior to stanford dining she spent nine years at the nationally acclaimed draeger's cooking school where she booked managed and taught classes and produced the cooking school's award winning magazine catalog which she used as a platform for topics such as michael pollan and educating consumers about food labeling cynthia is also a freelance food writer who has written over 150 articles for publications such as the san francisco chronicle and has edited books including hawaiian celebrity chef sam choy's poke cookbook as a human biology major at stanford she got her first taste of professional cooking by helping the chef prepare meals at the toyon eating clubs her multidisciplinary interests in food from sustainability to food science to food safety and passion for educating people about food has brought her full circle back to the farm stanford dining and the food summit committee
